Aol.name: Aol
Aol.description: Aol is a web portal and online service provider based in New York City. It is a brand marketed by Verizon Media.

Ask.name: Ask
Ask.description: Ask.com is a question answering-focused e-business and web search engine founded in 1996 by Garrett Gruener and David Warthen in Berkeley, California.

Bing.name: Bing
Bing.description: Bing is a web search engine owned and operated by Microsoft. The service has its origins in Microsoft's previous search engines: MSN Search, Windows Live Search and later Live Search.

Brave.name: Brave
Brave.description: Brave Search is a search engine developed by Brave Software, the company behind the Brave web browser. It is built on top of an independent index and does not track users.

DuckDuckGo.name: DuckDuckGo
DuckDuckGo.description: DuckDuckGo is an internet search engine that emphasizes protecting searchers' privacy and avoiding the filter bubble of personalized search results.

Goodsearch.name: Goodsearch
Goodsearch.description: Goodsearch is a search engine that donates a penny per search to a charity of the user's choice.

Google Search.name: Google Search
Google Search.description: Google Search is a web search engine developed by Google. It is the most used search engine on the World Wide Web across all platforms, with 92.16% market share as of December 2020.

Instya.name: Instya
Instya.description: Instya is a search engine that provides search results from various sources.

Impersonal.me.name: Impersonal.me
Impersonal.me.description: Impersonal.me is a search engine that provides search results from various sources.

Lycos.name: Lycos
Lycos.description: Lycos is a web search engine and web portal established in 1994, spun out of Carnegie Mellon University.

Mojeek.name: Mojeek
Mojeek.description: Mojeek is a web search engine based in the United Kingdom.

Search.com.name: Search.com
Search.com.description: Search.com is a meta-search engine that allows users to search multiple leading search engines at once, returning more comprehensive and relevant results fast.

Wolfram Alpha.name: Wolfram Alpha
Wolfram Alpha.description: Wolfram Alpha is a computational knowledge engine or answer engine developed by Wolfram Alpha LLC, a subsidiary of Wolfram Research.

Yahoo! Search.name: Yahoo! Search
Yahoo! Search.description: Yahoo! Search is a web search engine owned by Yahoo, headquartered in Sunnyvale, California.

YOU.name: YOU
YOU.description: YOU is a search engine that provides search results from various sources.
